gger.", "We intentionally merge all of flawfinder's functionality into 1 file", "so it's trivial to copy & use elsewhere."]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "flawfinder.Hit.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.__getitem__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.__eq__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.__ne__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.cwes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return CWEs"]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.fingerprint", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return fingerprint of stripped context."]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.helpuri", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Help uri for each defined rule. e.g. \"https://dwheeler.com/flawfinder#FF1002\"", "return first CWE link for now"]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.show_csv", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Show as CSV format"]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.show", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "flawfinder.Hit.source_position", "type": null, "documentation": ["By default, the second parameter is the source."]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.format_position", "type": null, "documentation": ["By default, the first parameter is the format."]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.input", "type": null, "documentation": ["By default, this doesn't read input."]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.note", "type": null, "documentation": ["No additional notes."]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.filename", "type": null, "documentation": ["Empty string is filename."]}, {"name": "flawfinder.Hit.extract_lookahead", "type": null, "documentation": ["Normally don't extract lookahead."]}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Each instance of Hit is a warning of some kind in a source code file.\nSee the rulesets, which define the conditions for triggering a hit.\nHit is initialized with a tuple containing the following:\n  hook: function to call when function name found.\n  level: (default) warning level, 0-5. 0=no problem, 5=very risky.\n  warning: warning (text saying what's the problem)\n  suggestion: suggestion (text suggesting what to do instead)\n  category: One of \"buffer\" (buffer overflow), \"race\" (race condition),\n            \"tmpfile\" (temporary file creation), \"format\" (format string).\n            Use \"\" if you don't have a better category.\n  url: URL fragment reference.\n  other:  A dictionary with other settings.\n\nOther settings usually set:\n\n  name: function name\n  parameter: the function parameters (0th parameter null)\n  input: set to 1 if the function inputs from external sources.\n  start: start position (index) of the function name (in text)\n  end:  end position of the function name (in text)\n  filename: name of file\n  line: line number in file\n  column: column in line in file\n  context_text: text surrounding hit"]}], "exports": []}]}